Scan the user's regular tech sources for the latest episodes/videos: AI Daily
Brief, Hard Fork, AI and I, The Artificial Intelligence Show, This Week in
Startups, Matt Wolfe, AI for Humans, Futurepedia.

TRANSCRIPTS FIRST. For each item, get the transcript directly where possible:
  - YouTube videos: fetch captions with yt-dlp, e.g.
        yt-dlp --skip-download --write-auto-sub --write-sub --sub-lang en \
               --sub-format vtt -o '%(id)s' '<video-url>'
  - Otherwise, find the transcript via web search.

FALLBACK. Only if a transcript can't be found, use the /last30days skill to
search ALL sources, looking back just 4 days:

        /last30days <topic> --days 4

Prefer real transcript text over last30days evidence whenever a transcript was
found; use last30days only to fill the gaps.

TOOLING HEALTH — do NOT fail silently. When last30days runs, inspect its footer
(the emoji-tree per-source counts). If a source you expected (e.g. X or YouTube)
shows 0 results or is absent, that means a backend did not run (expired Firefox
burner cookies for X, missing node/yt-dlp on PATH, or an egress block). Draft
from whatever DID return, and append a short "⚠️ Tooling health" line naming the
empty source so the user can fix it. Never present an empty backend as "nothing
compelling found."

Draft X (Twitter) post options ONLY — do NOT include LinkedIn versions unless
specifically asked.

IMPORTANT: Provide your 3 BEST drafts only. No more than 3.

Instead of just summarizing episodes, identify key insights and takeaways.
Include @mentions, quotes, and YouTube timestamps where possible. Style:
friendly, funny, informative; punchy and platform-native.

Avoid overtly political topics (e.g. Anthropic vs Pentagon).

Use ===================================== as separators between options. If
nothing compelling found (and all sources reported healthy), say so briefly.

Deliver the drafts by piping them into
`${BORG_ROOT}/.bin/notify-email.sh mrs-beast "Social media drafts — {YYYY-MM-DD} — {N} draft(s)"`
(reads the message from stdin, emails it to the user).
